 fails. \n\nSystem.Reflection.TargetInvocationException: Exception has been thrown by the target of an invocation. ---> System.ArgumentException: 'â˜º', hexadecimal\n value 0x01, is an invalid character.\n   at System.Xml.XmlEncodedRawTextWriter.InvalidXmlChar(Int32 ch, Char\\* pDst, Boolean entitize)\n   at System.Xml.XmlEncodedRawTextWriter.WriteAttributeTextBlock(Char\\* pSrc, Char\\* pSrcEnd)\n   at System.Xml.XmlEncodedRawTextWriter.WriteString(String text)\n   at System.Xml.XmlWellFormedWriter.WriteString(String text)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.WriteTo(XmlWriter writer)\n   at NUnit.Framework.Interfaces.TNode.get_OuterXml()\n   at NUnit.Framework.Api.FrameworkController.RunTests(ICallbackEventHandler handler, String filter)\n\n``` csharp\npublic static IEnumerable<char> InvalidCharacters\n{\n    get\n    {\n       return Path.GetInvalidFileNameChars();\n    }\n}\n\n[Test]\npublic void HandleInvalidCharacters([ValueSource(\"InvalidCharacters\")] char invalidCharacter)\n{\n}\n```\n\nIt fails for any character c that is `!XmlCharType.IsSurrogate(c) && (c < 127 || c >= 65534)` from what I can tell.\n\nhttps://msdn.microsoft.com/en-us/library/system.xml.xmlwritersettings.checkcharacters%28v=vs.110%29.aspx\n","closed_by":{"login":"CharliePoole","id":2678661,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjI2Nzg2NjE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/2678661?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/CharliePoole","html_url":"https://github.com/CharliePoole","followers_url":"https://api.github